uman life on earth. Offering sharp and surprising insights about a breathtaking range of authors, from Edgar Rice Burroughs to Kazuo Ishiguro, Willa Cather to Maggie Nelson, Novels by Aliens tells the story of how genre became mood in the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aExtraterrestrial beings in literature. 0aFictiony21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  anonhuman, novel, contemporary, genre, alien, Anthropocene, realism, materialism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226827841423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226827841/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles